":"/7XvomNV2M9UqZEa87IRk69F441R.jpg","original_title":"Apinan vuosi","original_language":"fi"},{"id":8417,"adult":false,"title":"Süss, the Jew","video":false,"overview":"Nazi historical drama about Duke Karl Alexander of Württemberg and his treasurer Süß Oppenheimer.","genre_ids":[18,36],"popularity":0.3165,"vote_count":45,"poster_path":"/3fN1p4OY7Mi0zXQqMJvCdhRwEYs.jpg","release_date":"1940-09-24","vote_average":4.3,"backdrop_path":"/4msV23h4lRFXQoOUUL8Oc0XTcxt.jpg","original_title":"Jud Süß","original_language":"de"},{"id":8434,"adult":false,"title":"Summer Things","video":false,"overview":"Two couple of friends, one very rich, the other almost homeless, decide to go on Holiday. Julie, a single mother, joins them too. Once at seaside, it starts a complicate love cross among them that will involve also a transsexual, a jealous brother, a Latin Lover and another nervous stressed couple. Not to mention about the daughter of one of them that is secretly in Chicago with one of her father's employees... At the end of the summer, all of them will join the same party...","genre_ids":[35,18,10749],"popularity":0.5336,"vote_count":102,"poster_path":"/laV4Xo5O1COZefAFPJLFZ28pkYS.jpg","release_date":"2002-03-04","vote_average":5.809,"backdrop_path":"/azkp4brPsmzJiyKw5ExkPDrVpWA.jpg","original_title":"Embrassez qui vous voudrez","original_language":"fr"},{"id":277352,"adult":false,"title":"The Passionate Adventure","video":false,"overview":"A rich man leaves his wife, poses as a coster, and saves a factory girl from a crook.","genre_ids":[18],"popularity":0.133,"vote_count":1,"poster_path":"/h1PZ9Wk4336u4vYcJup6CJtERt7.jpg","release_date":"1924-07-01","vote_average":6,"backdrop_path":"/e5C3lPya6prhtbXzMw1N0jgakc2.jpg","original_title":"The Passionate Adventure","original_language":"en"},{"id":277364,"adult":false,"title":"Promise at Dawn","video":false,"overview":"A single mother raises her son in impossible circumstances first in Leningrad, then Krakow, and then France, and is over-ambitious about him but never gives in.","genre_ids":[18],"popularity":0.1868,"vote_count":9,"poster_path":"/olkNCkEhhUiRuwMt6hcwxuchGf8.jpg","release_date":"1970-11-25","vote_average":5.3,"backdrop_path":"/symqYH29cghJJ9QlV4uHtUi5W51.jpg","original_title":"Promise at Dawn","original_language":"en"},{"id":661436,"adult":false,"title":"An Accident","video":false,"overview":"In the 1980s, the building themes were transformed into bipolar moral dilemmas involving overly ambitious individuals who wanted to excel at any cost. The hero is the head of a demolition crew that demolishes large buildings, initially a sympathetic young man who, in the pursuit of career and accolades, begins to transgress the boundaries of what was then called socialist morality and legality. He gradually finds himself at odds with the principles of ordinary but honest people. The narrative's bland, proclamatory film is closely connected to its time of creation, and there are hardly any more timeless insights to be found.","genre_ids":[18],"popularity":0.2402,"vote_count":0,"poster_path":"/iFKRA8kCddfN0B23EXbSW3sOgI4.jpg","release_date":"1986-09-01","vote_average":0,"backdrop_path":null,"original_title":"Havárie","original_language":"cs"},{"id":8338,"adult":false,"title":"Blindness","video":false,"overview":"When a sudden plague of blindness devastates a city, a small group of the afflicted band together to triumphantly overcome the horrific conditions of their imposed quarantine.","genre_ids":[18,9648,878,53],"popularity":6.034,"vote_count":1341,"poster_path":"/deBsx5IxyqCC217j3VY24TkkE0Z.jpg","release_date":"2008-05-14","vote_average":6.512,"backdrop_path":"/sN0czEtCT1jEFQVajWBsKwdFBKm.jpg","original_title":"Blindness","original_language":"en"},{"id":8741,"adult":false,"title":"The Thin Red Line","video":false,"overview":"The story of a group of men, an Army Rifle company called C-for-Charlie, who change, suffer, and ultimately make essential discoveries about themselves during the fierce World War II battle of Guadalcanal. It follows their journey, from the surprise of an unopposed landing, through the bloody and exhausting battles that follow, to the ultimate departure of those who survived.","genre_ids":[18,36,10752],"popularity":4.9213,"vote_count":3223,"poster_path":"/seMydAaoxQP6F0xbE1jOcTmn5Jr.jpg","release_date":"1998-12-23","vote_average":7.445,"backdrop_path":"/hsDyfAk2ml82IrpPC4AHvxvuTsn.jpg","original_title":"The Thin Red Line","original_language":"en"},{"id":8198,"adult":false,"title":"The Quiet American","video":false,"overview":"Cynical British journalist Fowler falls in love with a young Vietnamese woman but is dismayed when a naïve U.S. official also begins vying for her attention. In retaliation, Fowler informs the communists that the American is selling arms to their enemy.","genre_ids":[10749,53,18,10752],"popularity":2.2502,"vote_count":322,"poster_path":"/nLooNNrvzpf49G7HsB9siQT4036.jpg","release_date":"2002-11-22","vote_average":6.5,"backdrop_path":"/fay6quwuE1sqGJ7R9I2PH5SNmTn.jpg","original_title":"The Quiet American","original_language":"en"}],"external_ids":{"imdb_id":"tt7841496","twitter_id":null,"facebook_id":null,"wikidata_id":"Q51224874","instagram_id":"perdidalapeli"},"social_ids":{"twitter":null,"facebook":null,"instagram":"perdidalapeli"},"gdvg_id":148578,"wiki_plot":null,"wiki_synopsis":null,"wiki_episode_guide":null,"wiki_production":null,"wiki_cast_notes":null,"wiki_reception":null,"wiki_soundtrack":null,"wiki_release":null,"wiki_accolades":null,"release_dates":[{"iso_3166_1":"AR","release_dates":[{"note":"","type":3,"iso_639_1":"es","descriptors":[],"release_date":"2018-04-19T00:00:00.000Z","certification":""}]},{"iso_3166_1":"BR","release_dates":[{"note":"","type":4,"iso_639_1":"pt","descriptors":[],"release_date":"2018-08-08T00:00:00.000Z","certification":"18"}]},{"iso_3166_1":"IE","release_dates":[{"note":"","type":4,"iso_639_1":"","descriptors":[],"release_date":"2018-08-09T00:00:00.000Z","certification":"